{"word":"σύζυγος","slug":"σύζυγος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σύζυγος</b></el> <el>(σύζῠγος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:συζεύγνυμι'><el>συζεύγνυμι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>yoked together, paired</i>, <el>ς. ὁμαυλίαι</el> <i>wedded</i> union, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a wife</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:masculine'>masc.</a> <i>a yoke-fellow, comrade</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}